analysis: The documents in this cluster are primarily executive orders issued by Presidents Herbert Hoover and Franklin D. Roosevelt. They cover a wide range of topics, including appointments, land withdrawals, amendments to previous orders, and regulations concerning various government functions. Many of the orders cite specific statutes and legal authorities as the basis for the actions taken. Recurring themes include modifications to existing policies, establishment or alteration of government committees and positions, and temporary measures related to specific circumstances.
title: Governmental Administration & Regulatory Adjustments
